  "description": "Mallard-type duck with very dark body, contrasting with paler tan head and neck. Blackish cap and quite dark line through eye. Underparts rather uniform with only a hint of wamer brown on chest. Dark through vent. Tail dusky brown without white. When exposed, speculum blue with narrow posterior border. Normal anterior border. \u00a0No curled tail feathers. Bill seemed to be yellow- orange-olive. Size of male Mallard. Some internal markings on uppertail coverts and scaps noted.",
